history.content: While I am sure it is possible, I would highly recommend against it. I don't know exactly how these courses are ran during the summer, but both of them are very project heavy, and can require a great amount of time spent to get the most out of each course.

children.subject: Taking 160 and 169 together seems redundant. Both are design classes with a focus on projects and both classes are industry-oriented. In 160 you will develop a mobile app whereas in 169 you will develop a web app. Also, project-based courses, such as, hmmmm, CS 162, tend to have heavy workload. Unlike theoretical classes where you can, technically, cram for the final exams in two weeks, 160, 162 and 169 require a lot more energy throughout the entire semester, not to mention you are considering taking both in the summer.
